HEADWORD: Inchmeal
<hw>Inch"meal`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Meal</er>
a part, and cf. <er>Piecemeal</er>.]</ety> <def>A piece an inch
long.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>By inchmeal</b></col>, <cd>by small degrees; by
inches.</cd> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inchmeal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Inchmeal
<hw>Inch"meal`</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Little by little;
gradually.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inchoate</ent>⟦br⟧
